FBIS4-48703 "drafr101_e_94005" FBIS-AFR-94-101 Daily Report 25 May 1994 WEST AFRICA Liberia Nigeria Reportedly To Start Troop Withdrawal Nigeria Reportedly To Start Troop Withdrawal AB2505140494 Gbarnga Radio ELRL in English 1200 GMT 25 May 94 AB2505140494 Gbarnga Radio ELRL English BFN [Text] The ruling military government of General Sani Abacha in Nigeria has announced that it is beginning the gradual withdrawal of its troops from the ECOMOG [Economic Community of West African States Cease-Fire Monitoring Group] force in Liberia. Nigeria's decision to withdraw from Liberia follows the release of an embarrassing satellite-recorded account of the physical and partial involvement of Nigerian ECOMOG troops in the Liberian conflict against the interest of peace and the NPFL [National Patriotic Front of Liberia].
